<subSubSection pageId="197" pageNumber="476" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="197.[727,1321,851,1274]" lastBlockId="197.[112,1316,1288,1629]" pageId="197" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[728,1004,1044,1077]" pageId="197" pageNumber="476">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 98-5-122 mm, tail 71-5—-100 mm, ear 14-19 mm, hindfoot 20-25-5 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Kotosh Grass Mouse is a medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName box="[728,827,1245,1274]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="197" pageNumber="476" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. It 1s uniform dark olive brown, with no countershading between dorsum and venter; ventral hairs have dark bases; and tail is unicolored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
